All four living former US presidents, including Bush, Clinton, Carter, and Bush, have pledged support for the World Trade Center Memorial Foundation.
The memorial will honor the 2,749 victims of the 9/11 attacks, symbolizing the emptiness left behind.
A total of 31 individuals, including family members of victims, have been named to the board of directors.
The foundation aims to raise $500 million for the memorial and cultural facilities.
The memorial, designed by Michael Arad and Peter Walker, will preserve the memory of the tragic events of September 11, 2001, for future generations.
